{
  "stem": "2004.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My uncle Jacob and his oldest son, Josef, otherwise known as Joshi-- that's how he was known.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was nicknamed Joshi-- ended up in Lemberg, which at that time was occupied by Russia.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were on the Russian side.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And of course, his wife and the youngest son were in Gorlice, which was occupied by the Germans.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] They have-- the father-- I mean, Jacob and Joshi decided that they would like to be reunited with the rest of their family, so they have registered to go back.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They have registered with the local authorities-- with the local Russian authorities-- in Lemberg that they would like to reunite with their families on the German side.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Of course, the Russians took-- they registered them and told them, to the best of my knowledge, we will let you know when and if you will be free to go back to the German side and be reunited, but in the meantime, you have to stay here.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So they stayed there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In the interim, we lived in Krakow under the German occupation.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And sometimes-- now we are, the Germans came into Krakow sometimes, I believe it was on September 3rd, 4th, or thereabouts.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We were living in Krakow until some time in late 1939 or early 1940.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "A law, a German law came out that all these people who were not permanent residents of Krakow-- and I'm referring to Jewish people who were not permanent residents of Krakow, in other words the refugee, so to say, the ones that came to Krakow shortly before the war started-- had to leave Krakow.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they gave us, more or less, I believe, a week or so to get out of Krakow.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So we had to go somewhere.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
